Class FdfCommonServices

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fdflib.service.impl.FdfCommonServices
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FdfSystemServices, FdfTenantServices

    public abstract class FdfCommonServices
extends java.lang.Object
    Universal implementation of the 4DF API, allows querying across all Entity states that extend CommonState. Created on 6/10/15.

      • setDeleteFlag

        public static <S extends CommonState> FdfEntity<S> setDeleteFlag(java.lang.Class<S> entityState,
                                                                 long id,
                                                                 long userId,
                                                                 long systemId)
        Sets delete flag for entity. In order to record the date, time, user and system requesting the record be marked deleted, a new current record is created to contain this information (arsd contains the date/time, ared is left null, as would any current state). The previous current state is marked as history and ends as of the present date and time. Queries on the entity for times before the delete flag was set will return the entity state for the appropriate time period. Use this method for non multi-tenant systems.
        Type Parameters:
        S - The parameterized type of the entity
        Parameters:
        entityState - The Entity Type to mark deleted
        id - The Id of the entity to mark deleted
        userId - the userId of the user making the change
        systemId - the systemId of the system makeing the change
        Returns:
        FdfEntity that contains current and historical states for the saved entity

      • setDeleteFlag

        public static <S extends CommonState> FdfEntity<S> setDeleteFlag(java.lang.Class<S> entityState,
                                                                 long id,
                                                                 long userId,
                                                                 long systemId,
                                                                 long tenantId)
        Sets delete flag for entity. In order to record the date, time, user and system requesting the record be marked deleted, a new current record is created to contain this information (arsd contains the date/time, ared is left null, as would any current state). The previous current state is marked as history and ends as of the present date and time. Queries on the entity for times before the delete flag was set will return the entity state for the appropriate time period. Use this method for multi-tenant systems.
        Type Parameters:
        S - The parameterized type of the entity
        Parameters:
        entityState - The Entity Type to mark deleted
        id - The Id of the entity to mark deleted
        userId - the userId of the user making the change
        systemId - the systemId of the system makeing the change
        tenantId - the tenantId of the tenant making the change (if multi tenant)
        Returns:
        FdfEntity that contains current and historical states for the saved entity

      • removeDeleteFlag

        public static <S extends CommonState> FdfEntity<S> removeDeleteFlag(java.lang.Class<S> entityState,
                                                                    long id,
                                                                    long userId,
                                                                    long systemId)
        Removes delete flag for entity. In order to record the date, time, user and system the record be marked deleted, a new current record is created to contain this information (arsd contains the date/time, ared is left null, as would any current state). The previous current state is marked as history maintaining it's df flag of true which tracks the time that the entity was marked deleted. Queries on the entity for times when the delete flag was set will not return a current state for the entity, only history, queries on the entity after the delete flag was removed will have a current record and a gap in history during the time the entity was marked as deleted. Use this method for non multi-tenant systems
        Type Parameters:
        S - The parameterized type of the entity
        Parameters:
        entityState - The Entity Type to mark deleted
        id - The Id of the entity to mark deleted
        userId - the userId of the user making the change
        systemId - the systemId of the system makeing the change
        Returns:
        FdfEntity that contains current and historical states for the saved entity

      • getEntityBetweenDatesById

        public static <S extends CommonState> FdfEntity<S> getEntityBetweenDatesById(java.lang.Class<S> entityState,
                                                                             long id,
                                                                             java.util.Date startDate,
                                                                             java.util.Date endDate,
                                                                             long tenantId)
        Retrieves entity that has states active starting at or before at the startDate passed into the method and ending at or after the endDate passed. Will return current and historical data for the entity existing between these dates, but no history that exists completely before or after the range. If an entity has states that exist both inside and outside the range, only the ones existing within the range will be returned. If a entity has no states existing in the range then that entity will not be returned. Includes specified tenant (when using multi-tenant)
        Type Parameters:
        S - Parameterized type of entity
        Parameters:
        entityState - The entity type to query
        id - Id of the Entity to retrieve
        startDate - Start date in range to get entity state(s) within
        endDate - End date in range to get entity state(s) within
        tenantId - Id of the tenant to retrieve for (Multi-FdfTenant mode)
        Returns:
        List of type passed
